Beacons
=======

date

:   2015-11-13

summary

:   Bluetooth beacons

Bluetooth low energy (Bluetooth LE, BLE, marketed as Bluetooth Smart) is
a wireless personal area network technology designed and marketed by the
Bluetooth Special Interest Group aimed at novel applications in the
healthcare, fitness, beacons, security, and home entertainment
industries. Compared to Classic Bluetooth, Bluetooth Smart is intended
to provide considerably reduced power consumption and cost while
maintaining a similar communication range.

